OL,6,F"People with epilepsy can often feel
OL,7,Fisolated and alone because of the
OL,8,Fcondition. Traditional sports and
OL,9,Ffitness settings especially can feel
OL,10,Fintimidating. Having faced their own
OL,11,Fchallenges, it's inspiring to see how
OL,12,Ftheir first-hand experience of living
OL,13,Fwith epilepsy has shaped the safe,
OL,14,Fwelcoming space they've created for
OL,15,Fothers."
OL,17,FAccording to the charity Epilepsy
OL,18,Faffects around one in every 100 people
OL,19,Fin the UK and over 51,000 people are
OL,20,Fliving with the condition in Yorkshire
OL,21,Falone.
